---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTABand from '@/components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="RESP — Registered Education Savings Plan | Heidi Blondin Financial"
  description="Start saving for your child's education and collect the Canada Education Savings Grant. Learn how RESPs work with Heidi Blondin Financial in Kingston, Ontario."
>

  <section class="bg-brand-plum py-20">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-5">Investing</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-display text-white text-balance" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Registered Education Savings Plan (RESP)</h1>
      <p class="font-sans text-[18px] text-white/65 mt-5 leading-relaxed">
        Give your child a head start on education costs — and collect up to $7,200 in government grants while you do it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white section-gap">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-6" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">How RESPs work</h2>
      <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>An RESP is a registered account designed specifically to help families save for a child's post-secondary education. Parents, grandparents, or anyone who cares about a child's future can open one — and the federal government helps by matching a portion of your contributions.</p>
        <p>The lifetime contribution limit is $50,000 per beneficiary, and the plan can stay open for up to 35 years — giving families flexibility in timing their contributions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Canada Education Savings Grant (CESG)</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">The federal government matches 20% of your annual RESP contributions up to $2,500 per year — that's up to $500 in free grant money every year, and up to $7,200 over the life of the plan. Lower-income families may qualify for additional grant amounts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Canada Learning Bond (CLB)</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Families who qualify based on income can receive the Canada Learning Bond — up to $2,000 per child deposited directly into the RESP with no contribution required on your part.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Tax-sheltered growth</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">All investment growth inside the RESP is sheltered from tax until withdrawn. When funds are paid out as Educational Assistance Payments, they're taxed in the student's hands — typically at a very low rate, since students usually have little other income.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintSage p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">What if your child doesn't go to school?</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">If your child doesn't pursue post-secondary education, you have options: transfer the plan to another eligible beneficiary, roll the earnings into your own RRSP (if you have room), or withdraw the accumulated income — subject to tax and a 20% penalty on the earnings portion.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 bg-brand-tintPlum p-5 border-l-2 border-brand-plum/30">
        <p class="font-sans text-xs text-brand-ink/55 leading-relaxed">Mutual funds are offered through Investia Financial Services Inc. This article is for general information purposes only and does not constitute personalized financial advice. RESP and grant rules are subject to change by the Government of Canada. Please consult a qualified advisor before making any financial decisions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand heading="Start saving for your child's future" sub="Book a free consultation and we'll show you how to maximize grants and grow your child's education fund." />

</BaseLayout>
